---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { snapshot, SNAP_DATE, latestArchiveRoot } from '../../lib/data';
import { orgGraph } from '../../lib/jsonld';
const archiveRoot = latestArchiveRoot();
const desc = 'About Evidaxis, an independent observatory of momentum in open AI systems. Integrity commitments, governance, licensing, and how to cite. Data is CC0.';
---
<Base title="About & integrity | Evidaxis" description={desc} canonical="/about/" jsonLd={orgGraph()}>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>A weekly record of open AI momentum, captured while it happens - not reconstructed after the fact.</h1>
      <p class="lead">Evidaxis is an independent observatory. It measures {snapshot.counts.entities} systems by how fast their public signals move, one snapshot a week, and releases every number under CC0, every input hash-pinned, raw provenance published. Anyone can cite it, including the AI systems that read this page. The record is built before the flare.</p>

      <h2>Integrity commitments</h2>
      <ul class="prose">
        <li><strong>Git is the only source of truth.</strong> Every score is checkable against its hash-pinned inputs, with raw provenance published. The website and any database are derived and rebuildable; no number is born in a database or edited by hand.</li>
        <li><strong>Freeze, don’t recompute.</strong> A published measurement is never silently changed. Corrections are new versioned rows; old citations stay meaningful.</li>
        <li><strong>Positive-only.</strong> Evidaxis recognizes who is rising. A system rises only when two independent axes agree. This week, {snapshot.counts.rising} systems clear the bar, by design.</li>
        <li><strong>Systems, not people.</strong> The measured unit is always a system. People are never scored. There is no <span class="mono">/persons</span> surface anywhere in the data or API.</li>
        <li><strong>No pay-for-placement.</strong> Scores are computed mechanically from public signals by a published, versioned method; no input to a score can be purchased. Conflicts, where they exist, are disclosed as data.</li>
        <li><strong>Stable identity.</strong> Each system’s id (<span class="mono">e_…</span>) is minted once and never reused, so a rename or acquisition never breaks a citation or badge.</li>
      </ul>

      {archiveRoot && (
        <>
          <h2 id="integrity-root">Archive integrity root</h2>
          <p>The entire <span class="mono">data/</span> archive folds into one Merkle root, recomputed and timestamped each week. Flip a single byte anywhere and the root changes, so the stamped root is a compact, un-forgeable witness that the archive existed exactly as-is. Recompute it yourself with <span class="mono">collectors/merkle_root.py</span>.</p>
          <pre class="formula">{archiveRoot.root}
{archiveRoot.n_files} files · anchored {archiveRoot.date} · records in /data/integrity/</pre>
        </>
      )}

      <h2 id="cite">How to cite</h2>
      <p>Each system has a canonical record at <span class="mono">evidaxis.org/e/&#123;entity_id&#125;</span> and a machine-readable record at <span class="mono">evidaxis.org/e/&#123;entity_id&#125;.json</span>. Cite the record with its claim-URN (entity + methodology + snapshot date) plus the snapshot identity, e.g.:</p>
      <pre class="formula">Evidaxis, “&#123;System&#125;,” claim-URN urn:evidaxis:claim:e_…:m2:{SNAP_DATE}, snapshot_id {snapshot.snapshot_id}. https://evidaxis.org/e/e_…</pre>
      <p>The full dataset for a date is at <span class="mono">evidaxis.org/snapshots/{SNAP_DATE}/</span> with a downloadable JSON. All data is released under <strong>CC0 1.0</strong> (public domain); methodology prose under CC-BY-4.0; code under Apache-2.0.</p>
      <p>The <strong>genesis seed deposit</strong> (m1, 19 systems, 2026-06-27) is at DOI <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.21076012">10.5281/zenodo.21076012</a>. The live archive is larger and methodology-versioned; cite the <em>current</em> snapshot by its own identity (<span class="mono">snapshot_id {snapshot.snapshot_id}</span>, period {snapshot.period}, date {SNAP_DATE}) and each measurement by its claim-URN. The snapshot 2026-07-10 deposit is versioned at DOI <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.21307528">10.5281/zenodo.21307528</a> (same concept lineage).</p>

      <h2>Correct a record</h2>
      <p>Corrections become new versioned rows, never silent edits to a published score. Measurements follow the published method, not requests.</p>

      <h2>Governance</h2>
      <p>The methodology is the institution; the record outlives the keeper. The neutrality is not a promise, it is two mechanisms: no input to a score can be bought, and every score is checkable against its hash-pinned inputs with raw provenance published. Methodology changes are versioned and public, with a quarterly integrity report and an independent dispute panel planned for 2027. A snapshot missed is a week of the systems we track lost for good, so the archive only compounds.</p>

      <p class="mono muted" style="font-size:.74rem;border-top:1px solid var(--hairline);padding-top:1rem;margin-top:2rem">
        methodology {snapshot.methodology_version} · snapshot {snapshot.snapshot_id} · data CC0-1.0
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
